```markdown
<a id="ap-066"></a>
## AP-066: Unconstrained Flex Compression Breaking Identity Text

**Status: ACTIVE**

**Trigger:** A nav logo, wordmark, or identity line wraps to two lines when the viewport is squeezed. Typically: `white-space: nowrap` is applied to the *text child* but the *flex container* that holds (mark + text) has no equivalent guard.

**Why it's wrong:** `white-space: nowrap` on a text leaf only prevents text reflow *within* that node. It does not prevent a flex container from wrapping its children (e.g., logoMark + logoText) onto separate lines. The load-bearing guard must be applied at the **identity container level** — the element whose children form the complete identity unit. A child-only guard leaves the container free to stack those children even though the text itself doesn't reflow.

A secondary failure mode: the identity item has `flex-shrink: 0` but the sibling (tagline, nav links) lacks `min-width: 0`. Without `min-width: 0`, the sibling cannot shrink below its intrinsic content size, which forces the flex parent to either overflow or wrap — and wrapping breaks the logo.

**Navigation Identity Priority Rule (codified here):**
> Core identity chrome — the nav logo and name — is always **rigid**. It must never wrap, shrink, or reflow at any viewport width. Supporting text alongside it — a tagline, a role blurb, nav links — is the **soft edge**: it compresses, wraps, or truncates first. This is a design principle, not a preference. The user must always be able to see who owns this site.

**Correct alternative — full four-property fix on the identity container:**
```scss
.logo {
  display: inline-flex;       // Inner flex for mark + text alignment
  align-items: center;
  flex-shrink: 0;             // The flex PARENT cannot compress this item
  white-space: nowrap;        // The flex CONTAINER cannot wrap its children
  // Note: also add white-space: nowrap to the text leaf as belt-and-suspenders,
  // but the container guard is the load-bearing one.
}

.links {                      // The soft-edge sibling
  flex-shrink: 1;             // Explicit: this side yields
  min-width: 0;               // Can compress below intrinsic content width
}

.navInner {                   // The flex parent
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: nowrap;          // Make intent explicit — prevents future regressions
}
```

**Do NOT do:**
```scss
// Wrong: guard on the leaf, not the container
.logoText {
  white-space: nowrap;  // ← this only prevents text reflow, not child stacking
}
// Missing: white-space: nowrap on .logo itself
```

**Frustration caused:** 1 round. Logo "Yilan Gao" split to two lines at narrow viewport widths. See FB-146.

**See also:** FB-146, docs/design/navigation.md §4.7.
```

